On receiving this Letter of Presentation, the Archbishop, evi- dently suspecting no evil, ordered the customary Inquisition to be held as to the right of Patronage, etc, and it was taken at Exmin- ster by his Chancellor.

Qui dixerunt, per sacramenta sua, quod Dominus Willelmus Fitz Water supradictus fnit et est ipsius Ecclesie Pa- tronus, et ultimo presentavit ad eandem ; et quod dicta Ecclesia pro tunc va- cavit per mortem Domini Willelmi, ultimi Rectoris ibidem3 quodque Presen- tatus ad eandem est bone conversacionis et honeste, quatenus iidem sciverunt et audiverunt—Et subsequenter idem Cancellarius eundem Presentatum admisit ad dictam Ecclesiam, ut est moris.''
